                                                          [GIT]
git init        : Initialize a New Repository (*)
git status      : to check status of file
git add file1   : to track the file
git add *       : to track all files (*)

git rm --cached file1        : to untrack file
git rm --cached *            : to untrack all files
git commit -m "msg" file1    : to commit the file (*)
git log                      : to show commit info
git log --oneline            : to show commits on single line
git log --oneline -3         : to show lost 3 lines in single line

git config user.name "masthan"       : 
git config user.email "masthan@vali" :

           ------------------------------------------------- [GIT-HUB] --------------------------------------------------------       

git branch                      : to show list of branches
git branch branch_name          : to create a new branch
git checkout branch_name        : to switch to a branch
git checkout -b branch_name     : to create and switch to a branch at a time
git branch -m old_name new_name : to rename a branch
git branch -D branch_name       : to delete a branch

git push origin master     : code pushing to master github
git clone "copy repo link" : source code copy from github repo to local
git pull origin master     : source code copy from github file to local
git merge movies           : copy files from movies
                     (or)
git rebase movies          : copy files from movies
git revert movies          : un-merge movies file (delete)
git branch -m master main  : rename the branch master to main
git branch -D master       : to delete master branch


git stash       : to hide the files
git stash apply	: to get the hidden files back
git stash list	: to show list of stashes
git stash clear	: to delete all stashes
git stash clear masthan	: to delete particular stashes
git stash pop           : to delete last stash only.

Note: if the file is committed we con't stash them.

git fetch       : show the difference of content from files git hub to git.
git cherry-pick commit_id : merge particular file in branch
vim .ignore : ignore commit & track files.


------------------------------------------------








touch file1    : to create a file
git status     : to show status of a file
git add file1  : to track the file
git commit -m "msg" file1 : to commit the file

git log                : to show commit information
git log --oneline      : to show commits on single line
git log --oneline -2   : to show last 2 commits in single line 
git rm --cached file   : to untrack the tracked files

CONFIGURATION OF USER:
git config user.name "masthan"
git config user.email "masthan@gmail.com"

git branch                      : to show list of branches
git branch branch_name          : to create a new branch
git checkout branch_name        : to switch to a branch
git checkout -b branch_name     : to create and switch to a branch at a time
git branch -m old_name new_name : to rename a branch
git branch -D branch_name       : to delete a branch

GIT REBASE: used to add files blw two branches.
git rebase train
git rebase dth

git stash	: to hide the files
git stash apply	: to get the hidden files back
git stash list	: to show list of stashes
git stash clear	: to delete all stashes
git stash pop	: to delete last stash only.












